Switzerland's 1988 provisional current account surplus reached a record 12.3 billion Swiss francs ($7.46 billion) from a revised surplus of 11.3 billion francs in 1987, the Federal Finance Department and the Swiss National Bank reported. 

The government also said capital exports in 1988 exceeded capital imports by a provisional 20 billion francs, which represents an increase from the revised 14 billion franc surplus posted in 1987. 

In commenting on the current account surplus, the government said capital revenues in 1988 jumped to 19 billion francs from 15.7 billion francs a year earlier. 

